@Serena split-classification is occasionally failing on sandbox because after clicking the button to start classification, it can't find the classifying popup. Here's the latest example, and it looks like the failure before this was the same reason: https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/11780/overview/3022952a-05a1-42aa-b70e-89a5fe4077ff?roarHideRunsWithDiffGroupsAndTags=1. Maybe it needs to wait a little longer?

I see this is skipped in CI (for product reasons?) - do we also want to skip it for everything else if we turned it off because we just don't need to test it anymore?
split was skipped because it was broken for a while on crafting-aihub, but we should unskip it
